FBIS4-18954 "drweu070_l_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-070 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 SPAIN Further Reportage on Russian President's Visit Further Reportage on Russian President's Visit Kozyrev Urges `Caution' in Bosnia LD1104163494 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 11 Apr 94 LD1104163494 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network Spanish BFN [Text] In Madrid, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, who is accompanying Russian President Boris Yeltsin on his visit to Spain, has just referred to the situation in Bosnia. Over to the radio car at the Viana Palace. Angel Garcia, good afternoon. [Garcia] Good afternoon. Russian Foreign Minister Kozyrev said here at the Viana Palace that one needs to exercise extreme caution in the Bosnian situation, and he personally has conveyed his concern by phone to U.S. Secretary of State Christopher, with whom he spoke from here when the second attack on Serbian positions was underway. [Begin recording] [Kozyrev in Russian with Spanish translation] Making such a decision without counting on Russia means taking a very big risk. [end recording] [Garcia] According to Kozyrev, the NATO air strikes against Serbian positions could backfire because they might make the conflict worse. That is why he also described the decision as hasty. That is all for the time being.
